{"updated_at": "2012-01-31T09:03:06Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-01-31T09:02:38Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3735626", "id": 3735626, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4738", "issue_id": 4738, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/gregolsen", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "18bf599b887aeed411b29c3eaf7cf5a4", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/18bf599b887aeed411b29c3eaf7cf5a4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc9ea960c20279f3da87253e42bf7f161.png", "id": 287994, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/events{/privacy}", "login": "gregolsen", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gregolsen/followers"}, "body": "The problem is in `uniq` that was added to `ids_reader`. In previous version of `ids_read` there was no uniqueness.\r\nSee this line in collection_association.rb `relation.uniq.pluck(column)`. See commit 109db5a that introduced that change.\r\n`uniq` gives SELECT DISTINCT and that's why error is thrown.\r\n\r\nLet's ask @lest why he added `uniq` in relation.", "_id": {"$oid": "523821f7bd3543c15100ea26"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4738#issuecomment-3735626"}
